Zoo's eh? Funny, I would describe blue servers as Zoo's sooner than I would pvp servers. On blue servers you're confined and babysitted by GMs, much like animals in a Zoo are babysitted, fed, disciplined by game wardens. I would describe pvp servers as being in the wild. There's is little or no intervention by superior powers (GM). Arguments are settled by the players themselves in the form of pvp, without the need for GM intervention. Players that have done something wrong, like trained some are disciplined by their peers and not by a GM called to resolve the issue. More responsibility is given to the player to play fairly on a pvp server and it works, those that would train or grief have it done to themselves and most fefs are weened out early on on pvp servers.
