				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Aye, Aye, Ayyyeeee ....here we go  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" />  You're wrong imo in so many ways.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
<A HREF="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/support/customer_service/cs_rules_of_conduct.jsp">Blue Server PNP</A>(Also Applies to PvP generally)
<br />
<A HREF="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/vz_rule_sets.jsp">Vallon Zek Server Rules</A>(Team PvP, 8 level pvp range)
<br />
<A HREF="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/sz_rule_sets.jsp">Sullon Zek Server Rules</A>(Team PvP, NO level range)
<br />

<br />
They're for reference, just incase someone looking here didnt know the rules to each server.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Kuriosity:</span> </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Players are confined on blue servers as much as on Red servers, you break the rules on a blue server is the same as breaking them on a red server. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
First of all, players are NOT confined on pvp server as much as they are on Blue servers.
<br />

<br />
From Blue Server PNP Policy: </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">3. You must comply with arbitration for contested spawns.
<br />

<br />
There are cases where two or more groups wish to kill the same NPC or hunt in the same area. In these cases, the groups are required to compromise. 
<br />

<br />
If an equitable compromise cannot be reached between the players prior to EverQuest Customer Service Staff involvement, the EQCSR will mandate a compromise. Any such compromise is final and not open to debate. Refusing to abide by these terms will be considered disruption and may result in disciplinary action. 
<br />

<br />
It is therefore strongly suggested that the groups make every attempt to reach a compromise that they can live with prior to involving an EQCSR, who may mandate a compromise that does not suit you to the extent that a player-devised compromise would.
<br />

<br />
Note: A "group" in this case is defined as a party of one or more characters that are united in a common belief or goal and are capable of completing that goal.
<br />

<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
From Vallon Zek Rules:</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">On Tallon and Vallon Zek, PvP-related Play Nice Policy situations are expected to be resolved using PvP solutions. However, Non PvP-related Play Nice Policy issues, such as training, causing intentional experience loss, bind point, zone, and portal camping, as well as other various forms of harassment, are not permitted in the PvP environment.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
From Sullon Zek Rules:</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Rules such as the Play Nice Policy do not apply to this server when there is a PvP solution available. Characters have the ability on this server to deal with their conflicts through combat. Causing experience loss by 'training' NPCs on other characters would normally not be an offense that would warrant a warning this server. But training done to others on the same team, thus eliminating any PvP solution, is a violation of the Play Nice Policies. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Now, If you examine the rules given for "Contested Spawns" above for the Blue server and apply the 2 PvP server rulesets to it, you will clearly see that the ONLY recourse for someone not wanting to ashare a spawn on a Blue server is to summon a GM, which puts resolving the issues out of the hands of the player, whereas on the PvP servers if someone will not share their spawn the players on such servers have the option of resolving the situation by THEMSELVES, instead of calling in a GM.
<br />

<br />
Therefore players on Blue servers are confined by server limitations in the actions they can take when diplomacy will not work. Players on a PvP servers are NOT confined in this aspect as they can kill the opposing party, if diplomacy does not work. Now this has limitations, I agree, on PvP servers, such as a high level trying to take a spawn from a low level on Vallon Zek. The high level will not be able to kill the low level due to level range, but it is still an option to call in reinforcements to do the job and on Sullon you can of course kill them anyway as there is no level range, only team limitations.
<br />

<br />
Players on blue servers are therfore confined more so than players on PvP servers with respect to actions they can take.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Kuriosity:</span> </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If you believe that GM's babysit anyone on any type of server you're delusional. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
